A police officer died on Saturday after being hit by a speeding car as he was crossing the Nairobi-Limuru highway. Amos Ashioya of the General Service Unit was crossing over the wall that separates the dual carriageway when the car crushed him. He was tossed to the opposite lane and run over by another car on the busy highway. He died instantly. The vehicles involved in the Saturday incident sped off and their owners are yet to be traced. The body was taken to the Kenyatta University mortuary. Click here for the latest political news 